<HEADLINE>
<P>
98 HAITIANS TO BE RETURNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The U.S. Coast Guard said Monday that it would repatriate 98 Haitian boat 
people who had been rescued Thursday off the coast of Haiti. They will be 
returned to Port-au-Prince and handed over to the Haitian Red Cross, the Coast 
Guard said. 
</P>
