<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAIL BOMB KILLS MAN, INJURES WIFE IN COLORADO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man was killed and his wife was hospitalized in serious condition Monday 
after a mail bomb exploded in their driveway, hurling fragments nearly two 
blocks away. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators searched for clues to the origin of the bomb, which had been 
mailed last Tuesday in Colorado Springs and picked up at a post office on 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Police did not release the names of the victims. The woman, who has head 
injuries and a broken arm, is in the Army, stationed at Ft. Carson. Her husband 
was a former soldier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
