<P>
SADDLEBACK WINS CONFERENCE GOLF TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saddleback won the Orange Empire Conference golf title, its 13th in 14 years, 
beating Palomar by 14 strokes over 36 holes Monday at Singing Hills Country 
Club in El Cajon. 
</P>
<P>
 All six Saddleback golfers finished among the top 11 and the Gauchos wound up 
with a total of 759. Saddleback, Palomar (773) and Cypress (783) advance to the 
Southern California Regional tournament Monday at Santa Ana Country Club. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Beck of Orange Coast and Pat Backbom of San Diego Mesa shared medalist 
honors with a two-over-par 146. 
