 Intel, CNN Plan PC Experiment: Intel Corp. and Cable News Network said they 
will test live multimedia news services on business personal 
computers.Beginning in May at a number of test sites, business PCs on local 
area networks, known as LANs, will display CNN news programs. "CNN is 
constantly looking to expand delivery of live news and information to new and 
diverse audiences," said Tom Johnson, president of CNN/Headline News. The 
venture will offer the live broadcast of CNN and Headline News on PCs. Intel 
and CNN did not say whether the picture quality will be comparable to that of a 
television. 
