<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tara Oettinger 
</P>
<P>
 Foothill, Jr. 
</P>
<P>
 Track / Sprints-long jump 
</P>
<P>
 Oettinger's performance Saturday at the Orange County Championships was 
unprecedented. It's not just that she won county titles in four events -- the 
long jump, the 100, 200 and 400 meters -- but how she won them.Each of her 
marks is among the top five in the history of the meet. In the long jump, her 
specialty, she went 18 feet 2 1/2 inches. That's 9 1/4 inches short of her 
season best, but the third best mark in county meet history. Her 12.43 in the 
100 and 25.17 in the 200 were each the fourth best ever and in the 400, her 
time (57.72) was the fifth best. Other notables: 
</P>
<P>
 * Andrea Pickett, Pacifica, batted .778 with five walks and three RBIs as the 
Mariners tied first-place Kennedy and won two other games. 
</P>
<P>
 * Stefanie Noffsinger, Huntington Beach, pitched a no-hitter, striking out 13, 
in a 5-0 victory over Edison. 
</P>
<P>
 * Wendy O'Brien, Irvine, was named swimmer of the meet at the Foothill Games 
after winning the 50 (23.93) and 100 freestyle (51.98). 
</P>
<P>
 * Robin Tessman, Foothill, pitched eight innings of no-hit relief in a 1-0, 
12-inning victory over Canyon. 
</P>
