<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY / VENTURA ROUNDUP; COLLEGE BASEBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In another blow to the postseason hopes of the Cal State Northridge baseball 
team, shortstop Chad Thornhill might be out indefinitely due to an elbow 
injury. 
</P>
<P>
 Thornhill, a junior transfer from Fresno City College, was injured in a 
collision near first base in Sunday's 14-6 loss to Cal State Sacramento. 
Preliminary examinations indicated that Thornhill suffered a fractured bone in 
his right elbow, a school official said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Thornhill has ranked among team offensive leaders all season. He is batting 
.278 with 26 runs batted in. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA042694-0061 </DOCNO>
