METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: ANGELES NATIONAL 
FOREST; DRIVER SHOT ON HIGHWAY; LAPD MECHANIC HELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Pasadena man lost an eye Monday when a motorist stopped in front of his car 
on Angeles Crest Highway and allegedly shot him. Noel Milovic, 52, was in 
stable condition at Verdugo Hills Hospital, Sheriff's Lt. Jim Hays said. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Shinkman, 52, a mechanic for the Los Angeles Police Department, was 
booked on suspicion of attempted murder and held without bail in the 1:15 p.m. 
shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 "The victim was driving ahead of the suspect when Shinkman drove around him 
and then stopped, got out of his car pulled out a gun and fired four shots, one 
of them hitting the victim," Hays said. 
</P>
<P>
 He said two off-duty sheriff's deputies witnessed the incident and followed 
Shinkman to a service station in La Crescenta, where he was calling authorities 
to say he had shot a man. Deputies in another car called an ambulance. 
</P>
