<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS: ARCO REPORTS 40% DECLINE IN PROFIT FOR FIRST QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Citing low crude oil prices at the start of the year, Atlantic Richfield Co. 
on Monday reported a sharply lower first-quarter profit. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles-based Arco said its first-quarter profit fell more than 40% to 
$149 million, or 92 cents a share, from $260 million, or $1.60 a share, a year 
ago. Revenue fell to $3.93 billion from $4.67 billion. 
</P>
<P>
 Arco said earnings in its worldwide oil and gas exploration and production 
operations fell 54% to $82 million, while refining and marketing earnings rose 
about 2% to $95 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
