<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARKETS TO CLOSE IN HONOR OF NIXON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Major U.S. financial markets will close Wednesday as the nation observes a day 
of mourning for former President Richard M. Nixon. 
</P>
<P>
 The New York Stock Exchange, American Stock Exchange, Nasdaq, regional stock 
exchanges and commodities markets will close. Bond markets were expected to 
close, while banks and currency brokers are expected to conduct limited foreign 
exchange trading. 
</P>
<P>
 The Treasury Department said it will postpone its auction of five-year notes 
from Wednesday until Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
