<TEXT>
<P>
 Bid for America West Retained: An investment group will continue with its 
$245-million bid to buy America West Airlines after agreeing to new bidding 
provisions. The new agreement allows AmWest Partners to seek Bankruptcy Court 
approval for compensation up to $4 million if the Phoenix-based carrier, 
operating under Chapter 11 Bankruptcy Court protection, selects another offer. 
Last week, AmWest Partners said it might drop the bid after the Bankruptcy 
Court opposed a proposal that would have awarded the investment group up to $8 
million in break-up fees. 
