<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Texaco Inc.'s earnings fell 27% on lower crude oil prices. 
</P>
<P>
 Texaco earned $202 million, or 69 cents per share, on revenue of $7.43 billion 
in the first three months of the year. A year ago, the company earned $278 
million, or 97 cents per share, on revenue of $8.23 billion. 
</P>
<P>
 The White Plains, N.Y.-based firm's exploration and production earnings fell 
43% to $120 million. The refining and marketing profit rose 18.7% to $203 
million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
