<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Boeing Co. profit dropped 10% in the first three months of the year, partly 
because of fewer commercial airplane deliveries, the aerospace company said 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Net earnings were $292 million, or 86 cents per share, for the quarter ended 
March 31, compared to earnings of $325 million, or 96 cents per share, last 
year. Sales for the first three months were $6.3 billion, down from $6.6 
billion a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 The Seattle-based company delivered 82 commercial jets, compared to 93 in the 
first quarter of 1993. It still projects a 1994 total of 206 plane deliveries 
and $21 billion in sales. 
</P>
</TEXT>
