<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 DuPont Co., the nation's largest chemical company, reported a 30% gain in 
first-quarter earnings, reflecting strong gains in its key businesses as well 
as cost cutting. 
</P>
<P>
 DuPont reported earnings for the first three months of $642 million, or 94 
cents per share, compared to $493 million, or 73 cents per share, in the first 
quarter of 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 Excluding a $32-million non-recurring gain from the exchange of North Sea 
petroleum properties, the Wilmington, Del.-based company's first-quarter 1994 
net income was up 39%. 
</P>
