<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 California Commercial Bankshares: The Newport Beach parent of National Bank of 
Southern California reported first-quarter profit of $201,000, or 8 cents a 
share, nearly double the $102,000, or 4 cents a share, recorded for the same 
period a year earlier. Total assets dropped 8% to $320 million from $347.6 
million. 
