<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; FALL KINDERGARTEN REGISTRATION TO BEGIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Registration for fall kindergarten classes in the Garden Grove Unified School 
District will begin Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 A child must turn 5 on or before Dec. 2 to be eligible, without exception, 
said district spokesman Alan Trudell. 
</P>
<P>
 Parents must provide their local school with proof of their child's age, 
including a birth certificate, passport, baptism certificate, immigration visa 
or affidavit from the child's parent or guardian when no other documents are 
available, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 California law requires children to be immunized for polio, red measles, 
diphtheria, tetanus, whooping cough, German measles and mumps. Parents must 
provide written documentation of the immunizations from their physician or 
health care agency, Trudell said. 
</P>
<P>
 Immunizations are available from private medical doctors or at clinics 
maintained by the Orange County Health Care Agency. Parents should call (714) 
834-4722 for clinic locations. 
</P>
<P>
 Children should receive a checkup during their visit for immunizations. An 
examination given then will fulfill the legal requirements for a first-grade 
physical. The necessary forms are available at school offices, Trudell said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
