<HEADLINE>
<P>
TICKETS ISSUED FOR SMALL OIL SPILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Coast Guard is testing a program of handing out tickets when small oil 
spills occur. 
</P>
<P>
 Oil spills require a full-scale investigation by the Coast Guard, a procedure 
that can drag on before ending in hearings before an administrative officer. 
Hoping to speed up the process, the agency is launching a six-month test of 
issuing tickets in spills of 100 gallons or less in the port areas of Long 
Beach, Charleston, S.C., and Galveston, Tex. 
</P>
<P>
 When a spill occurs and the violator is known, the investigating officer can 
issue a ticket immediately under the program. The violator will be able to pay 
a penalty to close the case within 30 days or request a hearing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
