<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: MICROPOLIS REPORTS $9.76-MILLION LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Micropolis Corp., a Chatsworth disk-drive manufacturer, reported a $9.76 
million first-quarter loss, while its revenue declined 12% to $83.7 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said its performance suffered in the quarter ended April 1 because 
of higher sales of a less profitable disk drive, and continued investment in 
new products that have yet to generate sales. It also suffered $1 million in 
earthquake damage. 
</P>
<P>
 In the year-earlier quarter, Micropolis earned $1.46 million on $94.6 million 
in revenue. 
</P>
