<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: NEW IMAGE INDUSTRIES' INCOME TAKES PLUNGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 New Image Industries Inc., a Canoga Park maker of intra-oral cameras and 
related dental imaging devices, reported a loss for the three months that ended 
March 31 as its revenue declined sharply due to bad winter weather and the Jan. 
17 Northridge earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 New Image's fiscal third-quarter loss was $840,000, while its revenue fell 
25%, to $6.74 million.A year earlier, the company earned $1.93 million on $9.02 
million in revenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said its third-quarter results were also hurt by $650,000 in legal 
expenses over a patent dispute, a $300,000 reserve for older inventory and 
$350,000 for sales commissions from the previous six months under its new 
marketing programs. 
</P>
<P>
 Also, the year-earlier quarter figures include results from New Image's former 
subsidiary, Styles on Video, which was spun off to shareholders in March, 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 For the nine months, New Image's net income plunged 70%, to $1.26 million from 
earnings of $4.16 million in the same period a year before. Its nine-month 
revenue edged up to $23.1 million from $22.5 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
