REGIONAL EARNINGS: WELLPOINT HEALTH EARNS PROFIT OF $61.6 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 WellPoint Health Networks Inc., a Woodland Hills managed health-care company, 
said its first-quarter profit more than doubled on a 16% increase in revenue. 
</P>
<P>
 In the three months that ended March 31, WellPoint earned $61.6 million on 
$682 million in revenue. A year earlier, the company had net income of $26.2 
million on revenue of $586.9 million. Included in the first quarter of 1993 was 
a onetime, $21.3-million charge for accounting changes. 
</P>
<P>
 WellPoint said that as of March 31, its medical plan membership had increased 
11% from a year before, to 2.43 million. Its pharmacy membership grew by 41%, 
to 2.25 million, and dental membership rose 4%, to 424,000. 
</P>
