<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: CALNETICS POSTS 21% DROP IN 3RD-QUARTER EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Calnetics Corp., a Chatsworth maker of molded plastic components and other 
plastic products for industrial plastics and building materials industries, 
reported a 21% decline in its fiscal third-quarter earnings. 
</P>
<P>
 In the three months that ended March 31, Calnetics had a net income of 
$134,000 on revenue of $4.1 million. A year earlier, the company had a $169,000 
profit on $4.16 million in revenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Calnetics' nine-month profit was $366,000, up slightly from the $355,000 in 
net income in the same period a year before; its revenue fell to $11.7 million 
from $12.1 million, a 4% decline. 
