<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: ISRAELI COMPUTER FIRM OPENS CAMARILLO OFFICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JACK SEARLES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Armon Networking Ltd., a Tel Aviv-based producer of systems for monitoring 
computer networks, has established its U. S. headquarters in Camarillo. 
</P>
<P>
 Why Camarillo? 
</P>
<P>
 "Because that's where I happen to live," said Timothy Riley, the Israeli 
firm's vice president for sales and marketing. 
</P>
<P>
 Armon, founded in 1992, markets systems that help maintain the efficiency of 
networks linking companies' computers. The firm is partly owned by another Tel 
Aviv concern, RAD Group. "We're selling our products in a dozen countries," 
Riley said. "We're in a very hot field. Business is great." 
</P>
