<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; 19 GROUPS HONORED FOR QUAKE RESPONSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nineteen organizations and government agencies that responded to the 
Northridge temblor "beyond the call of duty" will be honored at a luncheon 
today by the United Chambers of Commerce of the San Fernando Valley and the 
Valley Industry and Commerce Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 The honorees are the American Red Cross, the Salvation Army, The Gas Co., the 
Southern California Regional Rail Authority, Caltrans, GTE, PacTel, the 
Metropolitan Transportation Authority, the Metropolitan Water District, the Los 
Angeles County Department of Health Services, the Los Angeles County Department 
of Parks and Recreation, the Los Angeles County Department of Public Works, the 
Los Angeles County Department of Social Services, the Los Angeles County 
Sheriff's Department, the Los Angeles Police Department, the Los Angeles 
Department of Water and Power, the Los Angeles City Fire Department, the Los 
Angeles Department of Recreation and Parks, and the Los Angeles Department of 
Public Works. 
</P>
<P>
 The luncheon will be held at Airtel Plaza Hotel, 7277 Valjean St., in Van 
Nuys. Cost is $25 per person. Blenda J. Wilson, president of Cal State 
Northridge, will emcee the event, which is open to the public, and present 
plaques to representatives of the honored organizations and agencies. MIGUEL 
BUSTILLO 
</P>
</TEXT>
