<HEADLINE>
<P>
BODY WATCH / DOWNTIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Having been earthquaked out of my cherished Santa Monica apartment, I find 
myself in a single room. 
</P>
<P>
 Without familiar possessions around me, I can still create my favorite, most 
soothing environment for being alone -- but not lonely -- as an escape from 
turmoil or fatigue: I semi-curl on the comfy studio bed, lost in a compelling 
story, munching comfort foods. 
</P>
<P>
 I've just finished "Clan of the Cave Bear," accompanied by assorted cookies, 
real cheeses, nuts, chocolate and savory crackers, munched to the hum of a tiny 
space heater to take the chill off. 
</P>
<P>
 -- BEVERLY CLOWER Santa Monica 
</P>
