<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOUNTAIN LION APPARENTLY KILLS JOGGER ON FOOTHILLS TRAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A mountain lion apparently attacked and killed a woman who was jogging on a 
rugged foothills trail. 
</P>
<P>
 The body of Barbara Schoener, 40, was found Sunday morning in the Auburn Lake 
Trails subdivision near Cool, about 40 miles northeast of Sacramento. 
</P>
<P>
 The body had claw marks and deputies found animal hairs that will be analyzed, 
said Lt. James Roloff. There were signs that her body had been dragged down a 
hillside, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Schoener, an avid jogger and marathon runner, went for a routine early morning 
run Saturday and failed to return home, deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
 Kevin Hansen of the Mountain Lion Foundation said mountain lions have attacked 
64 people in the United States and Canada in the past 104 years. About a dozen 
of the attacks were fatal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
