<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE TIMES 100 / POTPOURRI; QUIRKS, ODDITIES, TRIVIA AND OTHER TIDBITS ABOUT 
SOME OF THE COMPANIES FOUND IN THIS YEAR'S TIMES 100. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by DAVID OLMOS / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hasta la Vista, Baby: International Totalizator Systems may sound like Arnold 
Schwarzenegger's latest business interest, but it's actually a Carlsbad company 
that makes computer systems for racetracks and state lotteries. 
</P>
<P>
 On the Fairway: *Callaway Golf, *Cobra Golf, *Charter Golf.The stocks of these 
golf companies were hot in 1993. Callaway Golf and Cobra Golf make oversized 
golf clubs, while Charter Golf produces golf apparel. 
</P>
<P>
 Room With A View--Not!: You can see the airport-but not San Francisco Bay-from 
the corporate offices of Bay View Capital Corp., a bank holding company in San 
Mateo. 
</P>
<P>
 Cattle Drives, Campfires & Cowboys...: *Homestake Mining, *Tejon Ranch, *Adobe 
Systems 
</P>
<P>
 They Must Be Doing Something Right: Companies that ranked among the top 100 in 
profitability, total sales, market value, sales growth and employees: *Applied 
Materials, *Countrywide Credit. *Intel, *Oracle Systems, *Solectron. 
</P>
<P>
 Frank's Kind of Company: Dames & Moore, a San Francisco environmental services 
company. 
</P>
</TEXT>
